args: Happy Halloween, everyone! Now put on\nyour best costume, because it's time for\nanother fun holiday here at the Halidom!
Yes, of course. Have a pumpkin cookie.
Yaaay! Thank you! And might I say, your\ncostume is simply splendiferous!
It certainly is. What are you dressed as?
A researcherâ€”er, or something.\nHonestly, this is the only costume-like\noutfit that I own.
I realize I should probably be dressed as\na fiend or something more traditional,\nso I can change if this violates the rules.
Heh. I'm not wearing much of a traditional\ncostume myself. All that matters is that\nyou enjoy yourself in an outfit you like.
ARE you enjoying your Halloween so far?

Yes, well, I imagine you have many
demands on your time as the organizer
of this holiday, so there is no need to pay
me any mind.
And Fleur, you should get back to your\ntrick-or-treating before all of the sweets\nare gobbled up by Ranzal.
You bet I will! Happy Halloween, Sylas!
Well, just let me know if you need\nanything, all right? Goodbye, Sylas.
(Will participating in this Halloween\nfestival really help me complete my\nhealing aromatic?)
I'm sorry, but I could not save him.\nWords cannot express my sorrow.
No apologies necessary. You're the\nreason my pappy was able to pass on\npeacefully and without pain.
Thank you again for those aromatics.
(If I'd only finished my healing aromatic,\nI could have saved that man's father.)
(My research has allowed me to make\naromatics that aid with a number of\nillnesses.)
(But there are still lives that slip\nthrough my fingers... My research is\nyet incomplete.)
Thank you for everything, little Sylas...\nBe well...my child...
...I want to save people from suffering\nas my grandfather did.
But will I ever complete my healing\naromatic if I continue at this rate?
Sorry, but did you just say something\nabout healing aromatics?
I would love to hear more on the subject.

Oh, merely an old physician with time on
his hands. Now then, if you don't mind,
I'm fascinated by this healing aromatic
you were mentioning.
I never thought there might be other\noddballs like myself who sought to cure\nillnesses through aromatherapy.

Oh my, yes! I've been researching it on
my own for as long as I can remember.
To think I'd meet a fellow scent scientist
at this age. What a joyful day!
If I may ask, sir, have you by chance\nmanaged to perfect a healing aromatic?
Then you must tell me the recipe!\nPlease, I beg you!
Let me finish. I cannot tell you the recipe,\nbut...
I can teach you the essence of it.
You have clearly devoted your life to\nresearching this miracle aromatic.
Were I to simply hand over my recipe,\nall your work would have been for nothing.
But if I show you the ESSENCE of my\naromatic, you can use that as a jumping-\noff point for your own work.
(He is correct. If we combine the fruits\nof our research, we should be able to\ncraft the perfect aromatic!)
In that case, Doctor, please permit me\nto serve as your apprentice.
Doctor, is it? Oh, but I DO like the sound\nof that. Now then, what is your name?
Excellent. Well then, Sylas, today I will\nconfer upon you the essence of the\nhealing aromatic...
(Of all the things he could have told me in\nthat moment, I never expected him to say\nthat I should ï¼‚enjoy Halloween.ï¼‚)
(If it's a hint, it is one beyond my ken.\nYet I will not give up...)
I will come to understand the essence the\ndoctor spoke of and finally complete the\nhealing aromatic!
